    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-12-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-12-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="19"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d19">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Campbell</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 7.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State, <hi rend="italic"
                                    >Washington,</hi>
                            </hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-12-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 6, 1866.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I transmit for your information a copy of a
                        telegram<note n="*" xml:id="d19fn1">For enclosure see correspondence with
                        France.</note> of the 3d instant from Mr. Bigelow, at Paris, giving the
                    substance of a note to him from the French minister of foreign affairs in regard
                    to the military occupation of Mexico. From this it appears that the French
                    troops will be withdrawn altogether from Mexico in March next. It does not seem
                    necessary to modify the instructions heretofore sent to you.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lewis</hi> D. <hi rend="smallcaps">Campbell,</hi> Esq.,
                            <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
